### ============================================
### SmartBook API - Tests de Endpoints
### Usar con extension REST Client de VS Code
### ============================================

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000/api
@contentType = application/json

### Variables (actualizar despues de login)
@clientToken = {{login_client.response.body.data.token}}
@adminToken = {{login_admin.response.body.data.token}}


### ============================================
### 1. AUTENTICACION
### ============================================

### TC-API-001: Registrar nuevo usuario
# @name register_user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "fullName": "Usuario Test",
    "email": "test{{$timestamp}}@test.com",
    "password": "Test123!"
}

### TC-API-002: Registrar usuario con email duplicado (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "fullName": "Duplicado",
    "email": "admin@smartbook.com",
    "password": "Test123!"
}

### TC-API-003: Login como Client
# @name login_client
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "cliente@test.com",
    "password": "Test123!"
}

### TC-API-004: Login como Admin
# @name login_admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "admin@smartbook.com",
    "password": "Admin123!"
}

### TC-API-005: Login con credenciales invalidas (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "admin@smartbook.com",
    "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### TC-API-006: Login con email inexistente (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "noexiste@test.com",
    "password": "Test123!"
}


### ============================================
### 2. RECURSOS (GET - Publico con auth)
### ============================================

### TC-API-010: Obtener todos los recursos (como Client)
GET {{baseUrl}}/resources
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-011: Obtener todos los recursos (como Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/resources
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### TC-API-012: Obtener recurso por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/resources/1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-013: Obtener recurso inexistente (debe fallar 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/resources/99999
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-014: Obtener recursos sin token (debe fallar 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/resources


### ============================================
### 3. RECURSOS - CRUD (Solo Admin)
### ============================================

### TC-API-020: Crear recurso (como Admin)
# @name create_resource
POST {{baseUrl}}/resources
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
    "name": "Sala de Conferencias API Test",
    "description": "Creada desde tests de API",
    "location": "Edificio Principal, Piso 3",
    "capacity": 25,
    "isActive": true
}

### TC-API-021: Crear recurso (como Client - debe fallar 403)
POST {{baseUrl}}/resources
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "name": "Sala Prohibida",
    "description": "No deberia crearse",
    "location": "Ninguno",
    "capacity": 10,
    "isActive": true
}

### TC-API-022: Actualizar recurso (como Admin)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/resources/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
    "name": "Sala Actualizada",
    "description": "Descripcion actualizada desde API test",
    "location": "Nueva ubicacion",
    "capacity": 30,
    "isActive": true
}

### TC-API-023: Actualizar recurso (como Client - debe fallar 403)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/resources/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "name": "Intento de hack",
    "description": "No deberia actualizarse",
    "location": "Ninguno",
    "capacity": 10,
    "isActive": false
}

### TC-API-024: Eliminar recurso (como Admin)
### CUIDADO: Esto elimina el recurso realmente
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/resources/5
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### TC-API-025: Eliminar recurso (como Client - debe fallar 403)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/resources/1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}


### ============================================
### 4. RESERVAS
### ============================================

### TC-API-030: Obtener reservas (como Client - solo las suyas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-031: Obtener reservas (como Admin - todas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### TC-API-032: Obtener reserva por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-033: Crear reserva (como Client)
# @name create_reservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "resourceId": 1,
    "reservationDate": "2025-12-25",
    "startTime": "09:00",
    "endTime": "10:00",
    "notes": "Reserva de prueba desde API"
}

### TC-API-034: Crear reserva con fecha pasada (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "resourceId": 1,
    "reservationDate": "2020-01-01",
    "startTime": "09:00",
    "endTime": "10:00",
    "notes": "Fecha invalida"
}

### TC-API-035: Crear reserva con recurso inexistente (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "resourceId": 99999,
    "reservationDate": "2025-12-26",
    "startTime": "09:00",
    "endTime": "10:00",
    "notes": "Recurso no existe"
}

### TC-API-036: Actualizar estado de reserva (como Admin)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/reservations/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
    "status": "Confirmed"
}

### TC-API-037: Actualizar estado (como Client - debe fallar 403)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/reservations/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "status": "Confirmed"
}

### TC-API-038: Cancelar/Eliminar reserva (como Client - propia)
### Usar ID de reserva que pertenezca al client
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/reservations/5
# Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-039: Cancelar reserva de otro usuario (como Client - debe fallar)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/reservations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-040: Cancelar cualquier reserva (como Admin)
### CUIDADO: Esto elimina la reserva realmente
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/reservations/5
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### ============================================
### 5. USUARIOS (Solo Admin)
### ============================================

### TC-API-050: Obtener todos los usuarios (como Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### TC-API-051: Obtener usuarios (como Client - debe fallar 403)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

### TC-API-052: Obtener usuario por ID (como Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### TC-API-053: Obtener usuario sin token (debe fallar 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users


### ============================================
### 6. TESTS DE SEGURIDAD
### ============================================

### TC-API-060: Request sin token (debe fallar 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations

### TC-API-061: Request con token invalido (debe fallar 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Authorization: Bearer token_invalido_123

### TC-API-062: Request con token expirado (debe fallar 401)
### Usar un token expirado real para este test
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJleHAiOjE2MDAwMDAwMDB9.fake

### TC-API-063: SQL Injection attempt (debe ser sanitizado)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "admin@test.com'; DROP TABLE Users;--",
    "password": "test"
}

### TC-API-064: XSS attempt en notas (debe ser sanitizado)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "resourceId": 1,
    "reservationDate": "2025-12-27",
    "startTime": "09:00",
    "endTime": "10:00",
    "notes": "<script>alert('XSS')</script>"
}


### ============================================
### 7. TESTS DE VALIDACION
### ============================================

### TC-API-070: Registro con email invalido
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "fullName": "Test",
    "email": "not-an-email",
    "password": "Test123!"
}

### TC-API-071: Registro con password vacia
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "fullName": "Test",
    "email": "test@test.com",
    "password": ""
}

### TC-API-072: Crear recurso sin nombre (debe fallar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/resources
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
    "name": "",
    "description": "Sin nombre",
    "location": "Test",
    "capacity": 10
}

### TC-API-073: Crear reserva con hora fin antes de hora inicio
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservations
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clientToken}}

{
    "resourceId": 1,
    "reservationDate": "2025-12-28",
    "startTime": "15:00",
    "endTime": "10:00",
    "notes": "Hora invalida"
}
